<subSubSection id="C371650BCE1B7662FF2FF99FB05FFCDA" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="0" pageNumber="182" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD43680CE1B7663FF2FF99FB5F4F974" blockId="0.[136,1452,1662,1894]" pageId="0" pageNumber="182">Diagnosis. The new species is characteristic by: General colour yellowish brown, head with a wide Y-shaped dark brown patch, and bearing a small triangular brown marking forward of M-line; hammer drop-like, with rounded base and triangular tip in ventral view and the rectangular epiproct sclerites separated by a wide membranous band.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD43680CE1B7662FF2FF907B529FEAB" blockId="0.[136,1452,1662,1894]" lastBlockId="1.[136,1452,236,885]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="0" pageNumber="182">
Description. Adult. Body length (
<emphasis id="B91FEA92CE1B7663FDBDF906B33CF951" box="[559,572,1767,1790]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="182">n</emphasis>
= 4) 
<quantity id="4C939B65CE1B7663FDE6F907B20EF952" box="[628,782,1766,1790]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2349999999999999" metricValueMax="1.3199999999999998" metricValueMin="1.15" pageId="0" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="12.35" valueMax="13.2" valueMin="11.5">11.5–13.2 mm</quantity>
, forewing length 
<quantity id="4C939B65CE1B7663FC43F907B55FF952" box="[977,1119,1766,1790]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.08" metricValueMin="0.97" pageId="0" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="10.25" valueMax="10.8" valueMin="9.7">9.7–10.8 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 8.0– 
<quantity id="4C939B65CE1B7663FAC4F907B4A8F952" box="[1366,1448,1766,1790]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="0" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="8.9">8.9 mm</quantity>
. Body color yellowish brown. Head mostly pale with a wide Y-shaped dark brown patch, and bearing a small triangular brown marking forward of M-line (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1B7663FE2AF8CAB310F8EB" box="[440,528,1835,1860]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,218,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-381@1.[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov., holotype. A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: A =1.0mm; B=0.2 mm; C–D=0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367173/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="182">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1B7663FD8EF8CDB33EF8EB" box="[540,574,1836,1860]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[155,218,2014,2036]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,1159,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-408@2.[189,1398,1156,1980]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov. A–B. Head showing variations of colour pattern, dorsal view. C. Aedeagus, dorsal view. D. Aedeagus, ventral view. E. Aedeagus, caudal view. F. Hammer, ventral view. G. Hammer, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367175/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="182">2B</figureCitation>
), anterolateral part of Y-shaped patch obscure in a teneral male (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1B7663FB63F8CAB448F8EB" box="[1265,1352,1835,1860]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[155,218,2014,2036]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,1159,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-408@2.[189,1398,1156,1980]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov. A–B. Head showing variations of colour pattern, dorsal view. C. Aedeagus, dorsal view. D. Aedeagus, ventral view. E. Aedeagus, caudal view. F. Hammer, ventral view. G. Hammer, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367175/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="182">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); slightly wider than pronotum. Compound eyes black. Biocellate; antennae brown. Pronotum brownish with pale rugosities, rectangular, corners obtuse (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FE24FF0DB30BFEAA" box="[438,523,236,261]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,218,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-381@1.[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov., holotype. A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: A =1.0mm; B=0.2 mm; C–D=0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Wings transparent, veins brownish. Cerci brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD43680CE1A7662FF2FFEF1B593FE7A" blockId="1.[136,1452,236,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
Tergum 10 with a pair of dark brown subtriangular spines on posterior margin, obviously sclerotized, set far from each other, located close to paraprocts. Epiproct rectangular, medially interrupted by a wide membranous band. Paraprocts hookshaped, dark brown, curved forward; finger-shaped in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FCC6FEB5B2D8FEC2" box="[852,984,340,365]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,218,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-381@1.[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov., holotype. A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: A =1.0mm; B=0.2 mm; C–D=0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Figs 1B, 1D</figureCitation>
). Hammer basal half brown, anteriorly with brown extensions; generally drop-like, with rounded base and triangular tip in ventral view, apex pale and parallel-sided in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FE87FE7BB08DFE1D" box="[277,397,410,434]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,218,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-381@1.[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov., holotype. A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: A =1.0mm; B=0.2 mm; C–D=0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Figs 1C–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FE0BFE7BB0D9FE1D" box="[409,473,410,434]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[155,218,2014,2036]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,1159,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-408@2.[189,1398,1156,1980]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov. A–B. Head showing variations of colour pattern, dorsal view. C. Aedeagus, dorsal view. D. Aedeagus, ventral view. E. Aedeagus, caudal view. F. Hammer, ventral view. G. Hammer, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367175/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">2F–G</figureCitation>
). Everted aedeagus mostly membranous and unpigmented, ventrally with two oval lobes at base connected by a thin transverse brown strip, medially constricted, apex trilobed (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FB82FE5DB587FE7A" box="[1040,1159,444,469]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[155,218,2014,2036]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,1159,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-408@2.[189,1398,1156,1980]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov. A–B. Head showing variations of colour pattern, dorsal view. C. Aedeagus, dorsal view. D. Aedeagus, ventral view. E. Aedeagus, caudal view. F. Hammer, ventral view. G. Hammer, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367175/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Figs 2C–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
