<paragraph id="8BD43680CE1A7662FF2FFD8BB56EFD2E" blockId="1.[136,1452,236,885]" box="[189,1134,618,642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
Distribution. 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7610CE1A7662FEDEFD8BB08CFD2D" box="[332,396,618,642]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49AFF862CE1A7662FE08FD8BB0F4FD2D" box="[410,500,618,642]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF862CE1A7662FE6CFD8BB344FD2D" box="[510,580,618,642]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Hubei</collectingRegion>
). Elevation of habitats ranges from ca. 
<quantity id="4C939B65CE1A7662FC76FD8BB56AFD2E" box="[996,1130,618,642]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" unit="m" value="900.0" valueMax="1100.0" valueMin="700.0">700–1100 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD43680CE1A7662FF2FFD6DB099FD68" blockId="1.[136,1452,236,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
Etymology. The name separata (from the Latin word 
<emphasis id="B91FEA92CE1A7662FD78FD6CB252FD0B" box="[746,850,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">separatus</emphasis>
, means divided, separated) refers to the epiproct sclerites being separated medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD43680CE1A7662FF2FFD33B05FFCDA" blockId="1.[136,1452,236,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">
Remarks. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D03CE1A7662FDF0FD32B2E5FD45" authority="Mo, Wang &amp; Li, 2020" authorityName="Mo, Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[610,997,722,746]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galerispina">
<emphasis id="B91FEA92CE1A7662FDF0FD32B3F5FD45" box="[610,757,722,746]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">F. galerispina</emphasis>
Mo, Wang &amp; Li, 2020
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF862CE1A7662FBB7FD33B584FD45" box="[1061,1156,722,746]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, by having similar epiproct. However, the hammer and the shapes of the everted aedeagi of both species are distinctive. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D03CE1A7662FB1AFD14B41EFCA3" authorityName="Mo, Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[1160,1310,756,780]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galerispina">
<emphasis id="B91FEA92CE1A7662FB1AFD14B41EFCA3" box="[1160,1310,756,780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">F. galerispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hammer has a swollen apex in lateral aspect, and the aedeagus bears a cap-shaped patch of brown triangular spines (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B71CE1A7662FB6DFCF6B4A8FC80" author="Mo" box="[1279,1448,791,815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="183" pagination="565 - 572" refId="ref2330" refString="Mo, R. R., Wang, G. Q., Li, W. H. 2020. A new species of Flavoperla Chu, 1929 (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region of southern China. Zootaxa, 4732 (4): 565 - 572. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4732.4.5." type="journal article" year="2020">
Mo 
<emphasis id="B91FEA92CE1A7662FABEFCF9B462FC80" box="[1324,1378,791,815]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">et al.</emphasis>
, 2020
</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 2b–c, 3a–c), while the new species has the hammer parallel-sided in lateral aspect and the aedeagus lack distinct spines (
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FF02FCBDB007FCDA" box="[144,263,860,885]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,218,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-381@1.[189,1398,933,1833]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov., holotype. A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars: A =1.0mm; B=0.2 mm; C–D=0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">Figs 1C–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13502A05CE1A7662FE81FCBCB054FCDA" box="[275,340,861,885]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="2.[155,218,2014,2036]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,1159,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-408@2.[189,1398,1156,1980]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 2. Flavoperla separata Liu, Li &amp; Shali, sp. nov. A–B. Head showing variations of colour pattern, dorsal view. C. Aedeagus, dorsal view. D. Aedeagus, ventral view. E. Aedeagus, caudal view. F. Hammer, ventral view. G. Hammer, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367175/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="183">2C–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
